  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[pomodoro timer]]></title><description><![CDATA[this was an exploration into discord bots, and my first time making one. in a nutshell, check out my repository and add this to your discord…]]></description><link>http://blog.samheckle.com/pomodoro-timer/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.samheckle.com/pomodoro-timer/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 30 Aug 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;this was an exploration into discord bots, and my first time making one. in a nutshell, check out &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/theheckle/tanatimer&quot;&gt;my repository&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=746124476122398751&amp;#x26;permissions=2048&amp;#x26;scope=bot&quot;&gt;add this to your discord&lt;/a&gt;! if you want to see a new feature, please make an issue and i will try to get to it. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if you don’t know what the pomodoro method is, you might want to &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pomodoro_Technique&quot;&gt;read up on it&lt;/a&gt;. effectively, it is chunking out time so that you can work more effectively. most of the time you work for 25 minutes and then take a 5 minute break. so, i built a discord bot to help me with that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this blog assumes you have no familiarity with discord bots, so i will start with the basics (read: this was my first discord bot).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tools you will need:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/discord.js&quot;&gt;discord.js&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;npm install --save discord.js&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>